If you use absolute URL`s, than you need to change URL when the page is deployed on a server.
Absolute URL should be used like this:
    
    &lt;?php echo SERVER_URL.&#39;/CSS/Images/icon.png&#39;; ?&gt;

You must change the SERVER URL to your server IP address or domain name.

    &lt;?php
       define(&#39;SERVER_URL&#39;, &#39;http://8.8.8.8&#39;);
    ?&gt;

Try creating one more constant. In the case below, I will use INCLUDE_PATH as a constant. And set in it the default full URL of the folder where the page documents are, in which case I&#39;ll use as an example https://mydomain/
```
    &lt;?php
    define(&#39;INCLUDE_PATH&#39;,&#39;https://mydomain/&#39;);
    define(&#39;title&#39;,&#39;Martijns Forum&#39;);
    define(&#39;footer&#39;, &#39;*All the footer code*&#39;);
    define(&#39;header&#39;, &#39;
     &lt;div class=&quot;banner&quot;&gt;
        &lt;img src=&quot;CSS/Images/banner.jpg&quot;&gt;
        *All the other banner code*
     &lt;/div&gt;&#39;);
    ?&gt;
```

Now use the echo function and call the include_path constant on all page requests, in this case at the beginning of css. It would look something like this:


```

&lt;?php
require_once(&#39;PHP/config.php&#39;);
?&gt;

&lt;html&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
    &lt;meta charset=&quot;UTF-8&quot;&gt;
    &lt;title&gt;&lt;?php echo  title; ?&gt;&lt;/title&gt;
    &lt;link rel=&quot;icon&quot; href=&quot;&lt;?php INCLUDE_PATH; ?&gt;CSS/Images/icon.png&quot;&gt;
    &lt;link rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot; href=&quot;&lt;?php INCLUDE_PATH; ?&gt;CSS/style.css&quot;&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
    &lt;?php echo  header; ?&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;

&lt;footer class=&quot;footer&quot;&gt;&lt;?php echo  footer; ?&gt;&lt;/footer&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
```

